---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import heroPhoto from '../assets/headers/hero.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Alexander K Saeri — AI governance research"
  description="I direct the MIT AI Risk Initiative, building the evidence base that decision-makers need to manage the most important risks from AI."
>
  <section class="lead-block">
    <h1>AI risk research for decision-makers.</h1>
    <p class="lede">I direct the <strong>MIT AI Risk Initiative</strong>, building the evidence base that decision-makers need to manage the most important risks from AI.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="https://airisk.mit.edu" class="btn">Explore the AI Risk Initiative</a>
      <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Request a meeting</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Image
    src={heroPhoto}
    alt="Alexander K Saeri speaking at the EA Global conference, November 2025"
    class="header-banner"
    widths={[600, 1000, 1600]}
    sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 800px"
    loading="eager"
  />

  <div class="section" id="about">
    <h2>About</h2>
    {/* Portrait placeholder — drop a new image into src/assets/avatar.jpg, then reinstate <Image /> and .profile-header wrapper. See BACKLOG.md */}
    <p>I conduct and communicate research to help govern highly capable general-purpose AI. I direct the MIT AI Risk Initiative at MIT FutureTech, and hold positions at MIT FutureTech and The University of Queensland. I'm based in Melbourne.</p>
    <p>My methods background is in social psychology, applied behaviour science, implementation science, evidence synthesis, systems thinking, and survey research.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="airi">
    <h2>MIT AI Risk Initiative</h2>
    <p>I direct the AI Risk Initiative at MIT FutureTech. The Initiative is a research project that provides authoritative data and frameworks to help decision-makers across the AI ecosystem identify, prioritise, and manage the most important risks from AI.</p>

    <ul class="workstreams">
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Risk Repository</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">What are the risks from AI? Which are highest priority?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A common taxonomy and database synthesising over 1,700 risks from 74 frameworks, used by governments, standards bodies, and AI companies.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Risk Index</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">How are leading organisations responding to AI risks?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">Global expert prioritisation of risks and an assessment of how key actors across the ecosystem are managing them.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Mitigations Repository</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">What are the mitigations for AI risks? Which are most effective?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A database of AI risk mitigations extracted from research, policy, and governance frameworks.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Incident Tracking</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">Which real-world harms from AI are already occurring?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A collaboration with the <a href="https://incidentdatabase.ai/">AI Incident Database</a> to monitor and analyse documented incidents of AI harm, and estimate their reach and severity.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="workstream-name">AI Governance Mapping</div>
        <p class="workstream-q">Which laws and governance approaches cover which risks?</p>
        <p class="workstream-a">A collaboration with the Center for Security and Emerging Technology (CSET) to systematically map governance documents from the <a href="https://agora.eto.tech/">AGORA database</a> against risk and mitigation taxonomies.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>

  </div>

  <div class="section" id="ecosystem">
    <h2>Australia's AI safety ecosystem</h2>
    <p>Alongside AIRI, I help build Australia's AI safety ecosystem. I advise <a href="https://www.goodancestors.org.au/">Good Ancestors</a> on AI risk and mentor researchers and fellows in the community. I co-founded the Melbourne AI Safety Hub coworking space, and convened the AI Safety Unconferences (2023 and 2025) and the inaugural <a href="https://aisafetyforum.au/">Australian AI Safety Forum (2024)</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="publications">
    <h2>Selected publications</h2>

    <h3>Recent</h3>
    <ul class="publications">
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, Lloyd George, S., Graham, J., Lacarriere, C. D., Slattery, P., Noetel, M., &amp; Thompson, N. (2025). <em>Mapping AI Risk Mitigations: Evidence Scan and Preliminary AI Risk Mitigation Taxonomy.</em> arXiv:2512.11931. <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2512.11931">doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2512.11931</a></li>
      <li>Slattery, P., <strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, Grundy, E. A. C., Graham, J., Noetel, M., Uuk, R., Dao, J., Pour, S., Casper, S., &amp; Thompson, N. (2026). <em>The AI Risk Repository: A meta-review, database, and taxonomy of risks from artificial intelligence.</em> Patterns, 7(5), 101517. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.patter.2026.101517">doi.org/10.1016/j.patter.2026.101517</a></li>
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, Noetel, M., &amp; Graham, J. (2024). <em>Survey Assessing Risks from Artificial Intelligence: Technical Report.</em> UQ / Ready Research. <a href="https://doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4750953">doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4750953</a></li>
      <li><strong>Saeri, A. K.</strong>, &amp; O'Connor, R. M. A. (2023). <em>Applying AI to sustainability policy challenges: A practical playbook.</em> Monash University. <a href="https://doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/y75rq">doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/y75rq</a></li>
